definitions.definition: Having a legal or moral right or claim to something.
examples: As a natural-born citizen I am entitled to run for president.
If you were injured at work you may be entitled to compensation.
He feels entitled to other people's respect.

definitions.definition: Convinced of one's own righteousness ( self-righteousness ) or the justifiability of one's actions or status , especially wrongly so; demanding and pretentious .

secondary_definitions: Having a legal or moral right or claim to something.
